09:27.501 --> 09:30.335
 <i> Pop Pop, was getting an earful</i>
 <i> about his past.</i>

09:30.337 --> 09:32.470
  MURRAY: <i> You want to know why</i>
  <i> I slept with the lights on?</i>

09:32.472 --> 09:35.373
   <i> 'Cause you took me to see</i>
   "Psycho" <i> when I was nine!</i>

09:35.375 --> 09:40.378
 <i> You owe me $17</i>
 <i> for a lifetime of showering</i>
 <i> with the curtain wide open!</i>

09:40.380 --> 09:42.581
     Oh, you want a message?
     I'll give you a message.

09:42.583 --> 09:44.716
         I'll give you a big,
         fat message in your
         big, fat ears.

09:44.718 --> 09:47.052
 POP POP:
 <i> You think someone's gonna come</i>
 <i> after you in the shower?</i>

09:47.054 --> 09:50.255
  <i> Believe me, you have nothing</i>
  <i> anyone wants to see.</i>

09:50.257 --> 09:51.222
        (BEEPING)
                   Fine.

09:51.224 --> 09:52.724
              You want to talk,
              let's talk!

09:52.726 --> 09:56.828
     ADULT ADAM: <i> And, so began</i>
     <i> the great Goldberg</i>
     <i> answering machine war</i>

09:56.830 --> 09:57.862
         <i> of 1980-something.</i>

09:57.864 --> 09:58.830
     MURRAY:
     <i> And you were so God-awful</i>

09:58.832 --> 10:02.000
    <i> that none of my friends</i>
    <i> ever wanted to come over</i>
    <i> and play with me!</i>

10:02.002 --> 10:04.402
       POP POP:
       <i> Friends? I had to</i>
       <i> pay the boy next door</i>

10:04.404 --> 10:05.170
      <i> to be friends with you!</i>

10:05.172 --> 10:06.538
      <i> So, you owe me a nickel</i>
      <i> for that, too.</i>

10:06.540 --> 10:08.440
   ADULT ADAM: <i> What began as</i>
   <i> one simple call from Pop Pop</i>

10:08.442 --> 10:12.978
       <i> quickly spiraled into</i>
       <i> an endless volley</i>
       <i> of very hurtful rants.</i>

10:12.980 --> 10:14.212
    MURRAY: <i> There! I said it!</i>

10:14.214 --> 10:17.148
  <i> You're a crappy dad</i>
  <i> and even a worse businessman!</i>

10:17.150 --> 10:19.184
   POP POP:
   <i> You think I'm implying</i>
   <i> you're a disappointment?</i>

10:19.186 --> 10:22.687
    <i> No, no. I'm saying it loud</i>
    <i> and clear! Disappointment!</i>

10:22.689 --> 10:24.623
 Again with
 the farkakte machine.

10:24.625 --> 10:26.691
     I know. He's been tying up
     the phone line,

10:26.693 --> 10:28.927
            and I can't get any
            of my messages.

10:28.929 --> 10:29.327
 What? No.

10:29.329 --> 10:35.233
 I meant your dad and Pop Pop
 might be doing serious damage
 to their relationship.

10:35.235 --> 10:36.635
                  Oh, please.
                  They're fine.

10:36.637 --> 10:40.238
           You are a trash heap
           of a human being,

10:40.240 --> 10:42.707
       and even a worse father!

10:43.010 --> 10:44.776
              He meant that
              with love, and...

10:44.778 --> 10:47.479
            Ah, crap.
            This went bad fast.

10:48.815 --> 10:50.749
      ADULT ADAM:
      <i> It had been a week</i>
      <i> since the great Goldberg</i>

10:50.751 --> 10:53.318
     <i> answering machine war,</i>
     <i> and my sister was tired</i>

10:53.320 --> 10:55.954
      <i> of not getting</i>
      <i> any of her messages.</i>

10:55.956 --> 10:57.856
    ROBOTIC VOICE: <i> Tape full.</i>
            (BEEPING)

10:57.858 --> 11:01.326
 My God! This thing between Dad
 and Pop Pop has got to stop.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.528
       ROBOTIC VOICE:
       <i> Messages deleted.</i>
             (BEEPS)

11:03.530 --> 11:04.963
    ADULT ADAM: <i> Acting on her</i>
    <i> standard selfishness,</i>

11:04.965 --> 11:08.867
 <i> Erica decided to erase Pop Pop</i>
 <i> and end the war.</i>

11:08.869 --> 11:11.603
         Hey, I'm home!
         Nobody bother me!

11:11.605 --> 11:13.471
         I need to check
         my messages.

11:13.473 --> 11:16.074
       ROBOTIC VOICE:
       <i> No new messages.</i>
             (BEEPS)

11:16.076 --> 11:17.742
 Hey! Anyone call for me?

11:17.744 --> 11:21.179
 You know, like a telemarketer,
 wrong number,

11:21.181 --> 11:23.048
 angry grandfather?

11:23.050 --> 11:24.783
        Nope.
          Okay.

11:24.785 --> 11:25.150
            Good.
           Yep.

11:25.152 --> 11:27.819
    Very good.
 Guess there's no reason
 to tie up the phone lines now.

11:27.821 --> 11:29.521
               Yep.
 I mean,
 no call from Pop Pop

11:29.523 --> 11:31.690
 means you don't have
 to pay him the $17.

11:31.692 --> 11:33.391
       Yep, yep, yep.
       You won.

11:33.393 --> 11:34.559
      I won.
             Yep.

11:34.561 --> 11:35.960
           Big winner.
      You won.

11:35.962 --> 11:37.529
          Murray wins.

11:37.764 --> 11:40.665
     And that is how you end
     an answering machine war.

11:40.667 --> 11:44.035
      Well, I guess it is best
      for your father's sanity.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.336
 Sure, sure,
 that thing.

11:45.338 --> 11:47.739
 Also, I finally get to use
 the phone again.

11:47.741 --> 11:50.642
 Hey! What do you think
 you're doing, you moron?

11:50.644 --> 11:51.509
           Making a phone call.

11:51.511 --> 11:53.511
 Yeah. The machine
 is expecting a call.

11:53.513 --> 11:57.949
 No one goes near this
 or stands in this area. Out!

11:57.951 --> 11:59.651
         (RECEIVER CLICKS)

11:59.653 --> 12:01.753
       Okay. Why the hell
       isn't he taking the win?

12:01.755 --> 12:04.422
     It's like he wants Pop Pop
     to call and rant at him.

12:04.424 --> 12:06.424
 Crazy as it sounds,
 I think your dad

12:06.426 --> 12:09.994
 actually liked chatting
 with Pop Pop
 through the machine.

12:09.996 --> 12:12.230
 And now
 that it's done...

12:12.866 --> 12:13.865
 ...he's sad.

12:13.867 --> 12:16.201
           That's nuts.
           Dad doesn't get sad.

12:16.203 --> 12:19.337
       ROBOTIC VOICE:
       <i> No new messages.</i>
            (BEEPS)

12:21.508 --> 12:23.975
        ROBOTIC VOICE:
        <i> No new messages.</i>
            (BEEPS)

12:23.977 --> 12:25.376
              My God. He's sad.

12:25.378 --> 12:27.612
        ROBOTIC VOICE:
        <i> No new messages.</i>
            (BEEPS)

12:27.614 --> 12:28.913
           Fine.
           You made your point.

12:28.915 --> 12:31.883
        We'll get them together
        and end this,
        once and for all.

12:31.885 --> 12:33.118
        ROBOTIC VOICE:
        <i> No new messages.</i>

12:33.120 --> 12:35.420
 ADULT ADAM: <i> My sister</i>
 <i> was determined to end the war.</i>

12:35.422 --> 12:39.958
 <i> Meanwhile, my mom</i>
 <i> set off a nuclear bomb</i>
 <i> of embarrassment at school.</i>

12:39.960 --> 12:41.392
               There's the guy.
               Watch out.

12:41.394 --> 12:42.994
       It's the Fighting Quaker
       of the Month.

12:42.996 --> 12:45.230
 How is this a thing?
 What's happening to me?

12:45.232 --> 12:46.664
        What is happening is
        you're being celebrated

12:46.666 --> 12:49.434
  for your popularity
  amongst your fellow students.

12:49.436 --> 12:50.902
          And one of
          the delightful spoils

12:50.904 --> 12:54.105
         is that you get to sit
         at this special table.

12:54.107 --> 12:55.440
       It's for cool kids only.

12:55.442 --> 12:58.710
 First of all, I like eating
 in the computer lab.

12:58.712 --> 13:01.379
 Also, my mom clearly
 put you up to this.

13:01.381 --> 13:02.981
             (LAUGHS)
             Popular and funny.

13:02.983 --> 13:05.250
 Whatever. I'm going back
 to my computer game.

13:05.252 --> 13:08.019
 And I'm taking
 this disaster with me.

13:09.055 --> 13:12.223
 Where is he going?
 Why isn't he sitting
 at his cool new table?

13:12.225 --> 13:14.692
 Did you screw the pooch
 on this one, Andre?

13:14.694 --> 13:16.361
                  No! Probably.

13:16.363 --> 13:18.196
              Look. If the kid
              won't accept help

13:18.198 --> 13:20.398
            from his super-cool
            guidance counselor,

13:20.400 --> 13:22.634
                 then he's just
                 a lost cause.

13:22.636 --> 13:25.737
      ADULT ADAM:
      <i> But my mom</i>
      <i> was never one to give up.</i>

13:25.739 --> 13:27.705
     <i> When it came</i>
     <i> to her little schmoo,</i>

13:27.707 --> 13:31.142
    <i> she always had the drive</i>
    <i> to succeed.</i>

13:33.079 --> 13:35.647
         Oh, Beverly,
         you're so "Krafty".

13:35.649 --> 13:37.015
           (LAUGHS)

13:37.017 --> 13:38.850
           Say cheese.

13:39.586 --> 13:41.186
      MAN: I think we found
      the problem.

13:41.188 --> 13:44.189
 Looks like someone
 wanted a little cheese
 with their Apple.

13:44.191 --> 13:46.291
                  Nailed it.
          BALL: Oh, come on.

13:46.293 --> 13:48.927
        The sign clearly states
        no food in here.

13:48.929 --> 13:52.630
       You kids know the rules.
       You are banned
       for lunch hours.

13:52.632 --> 13:54.032
 But where are we
 supposed to go?

13:54.034 --> 13:56.334
           In the cafeteria
           with the normals.

13:56.336 --> 13:58.236
            Yeah, I said it.

13:58.238 --> 13:59.470
 Come on.
 I'll cut you a check.

13:59.472 --> 14:02.273
 No! You can't send us back
 in the wild!

14:02.275 --> 14:03.908
 We've been domesticated.

14:03.910 --> 14:04.542
              Guys, guys, guys.

14:04.544 --> 14:07.812
 I think the silver lining here
 is that Mike Z. talked.

14:07.814 --> 14:09.414
 You shut it!
 Shut it, Goldberg!

14:09.416 --> 14:11.716
 You know, it's kind of funny
 how the drive got cheese

14:11.718 --> 14:14.118
 just after you
 joined our crew.

14:14.120 --> 14:16.754
           Mike, Mike, it's me.

14:16.756 --> 14:18.323
              I... I wouldn't
              cheese the drive.

14:18.325 --> 14:20.758
         Well, me and Mike Levy
         are kosher.
 Way of life!

14:20.760 --> 14:23.328
 And Rog, Mink, and Alvie
 are lactose-intolerant.

14:23.330 --> 14:25.196
 Come at me!
         But every day,

14:25.198 --> 14:28.132
 you eat the same turkey
 and cheese sandwich.

14:28.134 --> 14:28.733
 Get some!

14:28.735 --> 14:32.136
        That is the lunch
        my mom always makes me.

14:33.607 --> 14:34.672
                    Mom!

14:34.674 --> 14:35.406
         (CROWD GROANS)

14:35.408 --> 14:38.142
 Boy, Al, we are lucky
 to get these seats.

14:38.144 --> 14:39.677
            Yep. Pure luck.

14:39.679 --> 14:41.379
          Oh, look who it is!

14:41.381 --> 14:44.515
   Hey, is that Pops and Father
   over there?

14:44.517 --> 14:48.152
         Well, this is a very
         unplanned coincidence.

14:48.154 --> 14:48.786
     Damn it.
                    Damn it.

14:48.788 --> 14:51.689
 Hey, now you two can talk
 in person like normal humans.

14:51.691 --> 14:52.790
 Pop Pop,
 let's trade seats.

14:52.792 --> 14:54.692
          That is a crap trade,
          and you know it.

14:54.694 --> 14:55.493
                 Mur, sit here.

14:55.495 --> 14:57.428
 I'm fine here on the end.
 Thank you.

14:57.430 --> 15:00.398
  Hey, Bar, tell Murray to flag
  down the soft pretzel guy.

15:00.400 --> 15:03.701
  Erica, tell Pops to tell Dad,
  Pop Pop wants a pretzel.

15:03.703 --> 15:09.374
    Um, Pops, tell Dad that
    Pop Pop would appreciate it
    if he bought him a pretzel.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.843
        Murray,
        buy your dad a pretzel.

15:11.845 --> 15:14.579
 Tell him to buy
 his own damn pretzel!

15:14.581 --> 15:15.380
             No go, Erica.

15:15.382 --> 15:18.416
 Barry, Dad kindly declines
 the pretzel purchasing.

15:18.418 --> 15:21.252
 Pop Pop, Dad said to get bent
 and buy your own.

15:21.254 --> 15:22.720
            I wasn't asking
            for a free pretzel.

15:22.722 --> 15:25.757
   Tell that ungrateful bastard
   he still owes me $17.

15:25.759 --> 15:26.557
           He can take it
           out of my tab.

15:26.559 --> 15:30.094
            Erica, Pop Pop said
            Dad's a bastard,
            and he wants a Tab.

15:30.096 --> 15:32.130
            Pops, Pop Pop wants
            a diet soda.

15:32.132 --> 15:35.233
      Murray, will you
      buy your dad a diet soda?

15:35.235 --> 15:38.036
           At the very least,
           it'll calm him down.

15:38.038 --> 15:38.269
    Fine!

15:38.271 --> 15:43.441
    Excuse me. Let me get
    a pretzel and a Tab
    for the old guy on the end.

15:43.877 --> 15:46.244
 Here.
    Here.

15:46.246 --> 15:47.979
        Here.
            Here.

15:47.981 --> 15:49.380
          What the (BLEEP)
          is this!

15:49.382 --> 15:50.648
    I don't drink ladies' soda.

15:50.650 --> 15:51.783
            Where's my pretzel?

15:51.785 --> 15:53.484
 It appears Dad
 is eating it.

15:53.486 --> 15:54.852
           You give your father
           a message,

15:54.854 --> 15:56.354
             and you tell him
             every single word.

15:56.356 --> 15:58.990
        ADULT ADAM:
        <i> Yep. Dad and Pop Pop</i>
        <i> were finally talking.</i>

15:58.992 --> 16:01.392
   <i> Only problem,</i>
   <i> they were using their family</i>

16:01.394 --> 16:03.995
     <i> as their telephone</i>
     <i> and answering machine.</i>

16:03.997 --> 16:04.696
                  That's right.

16:04.698 --> 16:07.398
        This woman cheesed
        the drive, not us. Her!

16:07.400 --> 16:09.200
      Whoa!
      That's a harsh accusation

16:09.202 --> 16:11.869
     against a faculty member
     who's here one day a week.

16:11.871 --> 16:13.438
 It's true. She cheesed it.

16:13.440 --> 16:15.773
 It's her signature
 culinary move.

16:15.775 --> 16:17.542
      Beverly, do you have
      anything to say?

16:17.544 --> 16:19.243
 I vehemently deny
 cheesing the drive

16:19.245 --> 16:20.678
 under cover of darkness
 when no one was here.

16:20.680 --> 16:24.182
      She said "vehemently."
      That's a big word.
      So I have to believe her.

16:24.184 --> 16:25.917
        Fine. If she's
        not gonna own up to it,

16:25.919 --> 16:30.221
     then I'd like to log
     an official complaint
     against this teacher, sir.

16:30.223 --> 16:30.888
       You mean your mom?

16:30.890 --> 16:32.590
 She's been harassing
 one of the students.

16:32.592 --> 16:34.058
              You?
 I don't see you writing!

16:34.060 --> 16:35.526
 Don't write it down, Andre.

16:35.528 --> 16:36.394
 Write it down, Andre!

16:36.396 --> 16:38.229
 Report the snuggies
 and the kisses,

16:38.231 --> 16:40.064
 both butterfly
 and Eskimo.

16:40.066 --> 16:41.699
             You Eskimo'd
             on school grounds?

16:41.701 --> 16:44.369
         Ooh! I gotta write it.
         I just have to.

16:44.371 --> 16:46.838
 School grounds or not,
 I am your mother,

16:46.840 --> 16:49.374
 and I have the legal right
 to snug, squish,

16:49.376 --> 16:52.410
 and kiss you like we're in
 an igloo as much as I want.

16:52.412 --> 16:54.812
    According to the school
    handbook, you really don't.

16:54.814 --> 16:57.915
       Oh, so it's almost as if
       there are boundaries

16:57.917 --> 16:59.550
         that no one can cross.

16:59.552 --> 17:02.487
      Check and mate.
      He's got you there, lady.

17:02.489 --> 17:03.888
 Adam, I just wanted you...

17:03.890 --> 17:05.490
                 Bup, bup, bup!
                 Boundaries!

17:05.492 --> 17:06.557
 You expect me
 to just sit...

17:06.559 --> 17:08.026
          Bup, bup! Boundaries!
 I just want...

17:08.028 --> 17:09.961
 Just give...
            Bup, bup, bup, bup!
            Bup, bup, bup, bup!

17:09.963 --> 17:11.662
  I want... But I...
            Bup, bup, bup! Bup!

17:11.664 --> 17:13.830
   I really think he wants you
   to respect his...

17:13.833 --> 17:14.965
 I know what he wants!

17:14.968 --> 17:18.803
           You know,
           I was actually happy
           in the computer lab.

17:18.805 --> 17:21.071
        Those guys accepted me.

17:21.074 --> 17:22.839
              You always say
              you want to help,

17:22.842 --> 17:25.943
            but you just end up
            ruining everything.

17:31.251 --> 17:33.951
     ADULT ADAM:
     <i> Realizing she'd made</i>
     <i> a mess of my social life,</i>

17:33.953 --> 17:36.487
       <i> my mom knew it was time</i>
       <i> to clean things up.</i>

17:36.489 --> 17:39.590
 Not so fast, Atkins. This is
 a random locker search.

17:39.592 --> 17:41.793
 If it's random, why are you
 targeting the guy

17:41.795 --> 17:46.364
 most likely to have a doobie
 hidden in his locker behind
 a Trapper Keeper?

17:46.366 --> 17:47.532
 Ah, nards.

17:47.534 --> 17:49.300
            Principal's office.
            Now.

17:49.302 --> 17:50.268
 This is so unfair!

17:50.270 --> 17:54.105
 It is, which is why
 I'll offer you a plea bargain.

17:54.107 --> 17:56.007
        You take the fall
        for cheesing the drive,

17:56.009 --> 17:57.508
        and this all goes away.

17:57.510 --> 17:58.576
 I don't know
 what you just said,

17:58.578 --> 18:01.946
 and maybe that's 'cause
 I've been hitting
 my Trapper Keeper,

18:01.948 --> 18:02.447
 but I'm in.

18:02.449 --> 18:04.515
          You also have to stop
          making fun of my son.

18:04.517 --> 18:05.983
  Done. Who is he?

18:05.985 --> 18:06.717
                      Adam.
 Adam who?

18:06.719 --> 18:09.353
     You know, the freshman.
     You call him a nerd loser.

18:09.355 --> 18:11.255
 That narrows it down
 to like 40 dudes.

18:11.257 --> 18:13.191
       The one with the dimples
       and the glasses.

18:13.193 --> 18:15.593
       He looks like a model.
       He plays with computers.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.428
 Oh-oh!
 That nerd loser.

18:17.430 --> 18:18.663
 Sure.
 I'll leave him alone.

18:18.665 --> 18:21.365
 Hey, little bro.
 How's it hangin'?

18:21.534 --> 18:23.034
          That's not my son.

18:23.036 --> 18:24.836
          Beat it, dork! Scram!

18:24.838 --> 18:28.539
 Ugh! I can't believe my arm
 just touched a nerd.

18:29.843 --> 18:31.275
 Getting rid
 of the answering machine?

18:31.277 --> 18:34.245
   Stupid piece of crap.
   Caused nothing but problems.

18:34.247 --> 18:35.413
 Don't throw it away.

18:35.415 --> 18:39.350
 Pop Pop did call back,
 but I erased the tape.

18:39.519 --> 18:40.618
         Why would you do that?

18:40.620 --> 18:41.853
 Because you were
 hogging the phone,

18:41.855 --> 18:44.188
 talking to your dad
 but not actually talking.

18:44.190 --> 18:47.692
 And then I realized
 not talking is how you talk.

18:47.694 --> 18:49.994
  Look. That's why
  we ambushed you at the game.

18:49.996 --> 18:52.230
 I thought maybe you guys
 would like to talk for real,

18:52.232 --> 18:55.766
   but if you like
   your machine better,
   then I won't stop you.

18:55.768 --> 18:59.470
     You know me and my dad.
     We never were big talkers.

18:59.472 --> 19:00.671
     Well...

19:00.673 --> 19:01.839
 Maybe it's time to try.

19:01.841 --> 19:04.375
    (DON HENLEY'S "THE HEART
    OF THE MATTER" PLAYS)

19:05.311 --> 19:07.245
                      You!
 Yeah. I was gonna call,

19:07.247 --> 19:10.348
 but then I thought,
 I don't know,
 I'd just come over.

19:10.350 --> 19:14.585
                  What for?
 I brought you $17
 worth of soft pretzels.

19:14.587 --> 19:16.487
  I wanted the money in cash.

19:17.824 --> 19:19.490
             But the game's on.

19:19.492 --> 19:22.593
              You could come in
              and, uh, watch.

19:23.429 --> 19:25.930
 Sure.
 I got nothing better to do.

19:26.966 --> 19:30.101
  Lucky for you boys, the real
  culprit stepped forward.

19:30.103 --> 19:34.172
 The lab's all yours again.
 Don't make crumbs.

19:34.174 --> 19:35.072
        (BOYS CHEERING)

19:35.074 --> 19:37.642
 Hey, sorry we blamed you
 for cheesing the drive.

19:37.644 --> 19:41.179
    It's cool. I'm just glad
    we're back where we belong.

19:41.181 --> 19:43.981
 ADULT ADAM:
 <i> From that point on,</i>
 <i> I couldn't wait for lunchtime.</i>

19:43.983 --> 19:48.819
     <i> And it was all thanks</i>
     <i> to someone who cared</i>
     <i> a little too much.</i>

19:49.222 --> 19:51.155
           Hey.
